<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-705-800  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 705 800.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  August 3 1990 n1482* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM sets major splash on distributed database.... (DB2 2.3)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   DB2 2.3 (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Distributed Data BasesMainframe ComputersData Base Management Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM SETS MAJOR SPLASH ON DISTRIBUTED DATABASE...andM;A year after its AD/Cycle extravaganza, IBM is planning a similar portmanteauannouncement of products, statements of direction and alliances in the fieldof implementation and management of distributed databases, Computer SystemsNews believes.andP;  The paper recalls that IBM's dream is a distributed databasesystem in which users do not need to know where the data they are requestingis stored, nor to worry about data integrity, and suggests that the new pitchwill be intended to fix in users minds the idea that the mainframe has acrucial role to play in distributed computing.andP;  The announcement will beaccompanied by a new release of DB2, 2.3, that will enable PS/2 users runningOS/2 Extended Edition to make unlimited read-only access to data stored in aDB2 database, and provide SQL/DS support so that users can make queriesagainst data on VSE and VM mainframes.andP;  The following release, version 3.0,is expected to enable OS/2 users to update DB2 data.andP;  IBM is also expected toannounce a data propagation manager that will enable users taking data fromboth DB2 and the hierarchical IMS to update both databases simultaneouslyrather than having to copy the updated data from one to the other.andP;  Observerstapped by the paper suggest that IBM will make a new round of investments insmall firms that can contribute to the overall concept, especially in thearea of managing enterprise-wide databases, and that it has held talks withLegent Corp, BMC Corp and Platinum Technology Inc to discuss its plans.andO;</TEXT></DOC>